 of actors not so few as to lack any claim to legitimacy yet not so numerous as to lack the ability to respond to urgent challenges in a timely fashion as a zone of policy opportunity focality is both promising and problematic in the face of a crisis a few authorized deciders can take steps that are necessary but controversial achieving a productive trade off between effectiveness and representation there is also a natural focality that can encourage pragmatism among formerly partisan incumbents who face the need to govern but they may not be able to agree and even if they can they risk being targeted for elitism unaccountability incompetence self dealing and intransigence among other sins by those who reject their authority to act the essay is scheduled to appear in the august 2011 inaugural issue of strategic review the indonesian journal of leadership policy and world affairs an english language journal of world affairs based in jakarta indonesia and is posted here with the publisher's permission download pdf+ the problem and promise of focality in world affairs complete article modified august 2011 pdf focality 4dist jul2011 pdf 175.7 kb topics east asia & the pacific indonesia search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages publications of interest dollar and yen the problem of financial adjustment between the united states and japan ronald i mckinnon shorenstein aparc 1993 after accession to the wto corn trade within china and between china and the rest of the world scott rozelle jikun huang us grains council 2003 pdf+ asean's pattaya problem donald k emmerson asiatimes online 2009 pdf+ hindering trade or protecting the developing world assessing the impact of the biosafety protocol for the case of china scott rozelle jikun huang delian zhang jun yang nicholas kalaitzandonakes 2006 pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies enc